In the XUV and SXR range, the absorption of almost all materials is typically very high. Therefore, cross-sectional imaging is only feasible in spectral transmission windows of the sample’s main materials. Luckily, many materials have such transmission windows. Two of them have conspicuous application potential. On one hand, silicon has a transmission window from λ=12\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
